BRAZIL DAYBOOK: Anbima Investment Fund Conference in Sao Paulo

-- B y   H e l d e r   M a r i n h o
-- 
2011-05-18T03:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-18/brazil-daybook-anbima-investment-fund-conference-in-sao-paulo.html
Brazil ’s capital markets association,
known as Anbima, holds a conference in  Sao Paulo  on investment
funds, with Maria Helena Santana, president of the country’s
securities regulator CVM, Bradesco Asset Management’s Director
Joaquim Levy and HSBC Asset Management head Pedro Bastos, among
others. Starting at 9 a.m.  GOVERNMENT:
*President Dilma Rousseff meets with Agricultural Development
Minister Afonso Florence at 11 a.m. and Queen Silvia of  Sweden 
at 4 p.m.
*Finance Minister Guido Mantega has a meeting with governor of
Brazil’s South and Southeast regions in the afternoon.
*Central bank president Alexandre Tombini meets his Nigerian
counterpart Sanusi Lamido in Brasilia in the afternoon.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*Petrobras executives meet with investors in Sao Paulo at 10
a.m.
*Datagro president Plinio Nastari and Banco Pine Chief Financial
Officer Marco Antonio Macielare are among the speakers at the
ISO Datagro New York Sugar Conference 2011, starting at 7:30
a.m.
*BNDES President  Luciano Coutinho  speaks to reporters in  London 
at 8 a.m. local time.
*Public hearing at the Lower House about air transportation,
with executives of Brazilian airlines, starting at 2 p.m.  ECONOMY:
*FGV preview of broad inflation index IGP-M at 8 a.m.
*Central bank economic activity index at 12:30 p.m.  EQUITIES:
*Eletrobras (ELET6 BS) is interested in buying shares in EDP’s
Brazil unit (ENBR3 BS)
*BrasilAgro (AGRO3 BS) scraps share sale on market condition
*JHSF (JHSF3 BS) gained as quarterly profit jumped sixfold  MARKETS
*The Bovespa index rose 1.3 percent to 63,673.34.
*The real rose 1.2 percent to 1.6156 per dollar.  To contact the reporter on this story:
